{
  "texts": [
    "At the time of the initial proposal of the RALM architecture, the majority of researchers employed generalized benchmarks.",
    "However, as the RALM architecture evolved, there was a growing number of RALM-specific evaluation methods and baselines proposed.",
    "Table 3 demonstrates the details of each evaluation model.",
    "RAGAS (Es et al., 2023) employs the WikiEval Dataset to assess the faithfulness, answer relevance, and context relevance of RALMs.",
    "Faithfulness is defined as the degree to which responses align with the provided context."
  ]
}